<item>
            <title>[LU-20075] lfs getstripe --ost errors</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20075</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There appears to be some mismatch in the arguments for lfs getstripe.&#160; Running the command &quot;lfs getstripe --ost fileName&quot; results in the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;usage getstripe &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&#8211;ost| -O UUID&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; ....&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This conflicts with &quot;man lfs getstripe&quot; which has the followinig ( does not require UUID arg)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;--ost|-O&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160;Print the starting OST index for the file layout&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;man lfs getstripe&quot; also has the following&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;--stripe-index|-i&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160; &#160;Print the starting OST index for the file layout&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t the &quot;getstripe --ost&quot; report the list of OSTs in the component and not be a duplicate option for --stripe-index, and why does the failed &quot;lfs getstripe&quot; indicate that --ost requires an argument, but &quot;man lfs getstripe&quot; does not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
